2.1 Model

k <- c(21,17,21,18,22,31,31,34,34,35,35,36,39,36,35)
p <- length(k) #number of people
n <- 40 # number of questions

data <- list("p", "k", "n") # to be passed on to JAGS
myinits <-  list(
  list(mu = 0.75, lambda = 1, z = round(runif(p)),
       muprior = 0.75, lambdaprior = 1)) # Initial group assignment

# parameters to be monitored:   
parameters <- c("predphi","phi","theta","z","mu","sigma","priorpredphi")

Exams_1.txt(6.1) , phi , theta . 8~15 phi theta . phi , .

predphi \(\psi\) predictive posterior distribution. predictive prior distribution priorpredphi .

Exam_2.txt sensoring I() , Exam_2J.txt truncation T() . Part II. 5.5, 70 Censored Data( ) . Exam_2.txt , Exam_2J.txt .

, 6.6 Gaussian sensoring 0 1 Beta . WinBUGS JAGS censoring truncation (90 )

model_text <- "
# Exam Scores With Individual Differences
model{
  # Each Person Belongs To One Of Two Latent Groups
  for (i in 1:p){
    z[i] ~ dbern(0.5)
  }

  # First Group Guesses
  psi <- 0.5

  # The Second Group Allows Individual Differences
  for (i in 1:p){
    # Second Group Drawn From A Censored Gaussian Distribution
    phi[i] ~ dnorm(mu,lambda)T(0,1)
  }   

  # Data Follow Binomial With Rate Given By Each Person's Group Assignment
  for (i in 1:p){
    theta[i] <- equals(z[i],0)*psi+equals(z[i],1)*phi[i]
    k[i] ~ dbin(theta[i],n)
  }

  # Second Group Mean, Precision (And Standard Deviation)
  mu ~ dbeta(1,1)T(.5,1) # >0.5 Average Success Rate
  lambda ~ dgamma(.01,.01)
  sigma <- 1/sqrt(lambda) 

  muprior ~ dbeta(1,1)T(.5,1)
  lambdaprior ~ dgamma(.01, .01) # .001, .001 . 

  # Posterior Predictive For Second Group
  predphi ~ dnorm(mu,lambda)T(0,1)
  
  # Prior Predictive
  priorpredphi ~ dnorm(muprior,lambdaprior)T(0,1)
}
"

samples <- jags(data, inits=myinits, parameters,
                model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
                n.chains=1, n.iter=2000, 
                n.burnin=1, n.thin=1, DIC=T)

p1 %>% pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("z"),
                    names_to = "SID",
                    values_to = "Value") %>% 
  group_by(SID) %>% 
  summarise(Mean = mean(Value),
            SD = sd(Value)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  separate(col = 'SID', c(NA, "Participant")) %>% 
  mutate(Participant = as.numeric(Participant)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Participant, y = Mean)) +
  geom_point(color = "darkred", size = 3) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=ifelse(Mean-SD<0,0,Mean-SD), 
                    ymax=ifelse(Mean+SD>1,1,Mean+SD)), width=.2, color = "darkred") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1, 15, by = 1)) +
  labs(title = expression(paste(italic(z)[i]))) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
